\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 REITs are often valued based on their price-to-funds from operations ratio. Enterprise value-to-EBIDTA (EV/EBITDA) ratios are typically used to value companies with large depreciation expenses (e.g., industrials). PE-to-Growth ratios (PEGs) are used for rapidly growing industries and industries where the price-to-earnings ratios (PEs) are disparate. Price-to-sales ratios are used to evaluate companies with low or negative earnings (e.g., start-ups).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa272\partightenfactor0

