\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 Oliver's offer has decreased to $28 per share ($35 x .8 shares). Cromwell's book value is $500 million ($800 million total assets - $300 million total liabilities) and since there are 45 million shares outstanding, the book value per share is $11.11. Based on a multiple of 2.5x book value, Cromwell's price is $27.78 ($11.11 x 2.5). Oliver's original offer was $28.50 ($35 x .7 + $4) and is actually slightly higher than its revised offer. Either way, both offers are greater than the price based on 2.5x book value and meet Cromwell's terms.\
