\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 Ownership levels of 20% to 50% use the equity accounting method for minority ownership. Investments are carried as an asset. When ownership exceeds 50%, consolidation is used for accounting. The assets, liabilities, and shareholder's equity are reflected in a single balance sheet. Each section of the balance sheet would increase. The ownership of the majority owned company is included in the equity section of the balance sheet. The portion representing minority ownership is recorded as an equity item called non-controlling interest (NCI). It was formerly recorded as a liability item called minority interest under older accounting rules.\
