\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 The formula to calculate return on capital or return on invested capital is EBIT or operating income multiplied by the complement of the tax rate, which is then divided by capital or invested capital. Although there are numerous formulas used to calculate capital or invested capital, based on the information given in this question, we would use total debt and equity. $365 million x (1.00 \uc0\u8722  .35) is equal to $237.25 million. Total capital is $775 million ($450 + $325). The return on capital is 30% ($237.25 million / $775 million).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa272\partightenfactor0

