\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 The company's interest expense would decline from $33 MM ($300 MM x 11%) to $21 MM ($300 MM x 7%). The net income would increase by the decline in interest payments multiplied by the complement of the tax rate. The decline is $12 MM and the complement of the tax rate is .79 (1.00 - 21%); therefore, the net income would increase by $9.48 MM ($12 MM x .79)\
