\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 Earnings yield is calculated by dividing the earnings per share into the price per share. It represents the amount of earnings that one dollar of investment will purchase. The earnings yield is also the reciprocal of the price-to-earnings ratio. A quick method to calculate this is to divide the dividend yield by the dividend payout ratio. 1.8% divided by 35% equals 5.14%. Additionally, the P/E ratio can be determined by dividing 1 by the earnings yield. The P/E for MSS is 19.45 (1.0 / 5.14%).\
