\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 Precedent transaction analysis, or M&A comparable analysis, is a valuation method that is used to value a company by comparing it to the transactional value of other companies in the same or similar industry sector. This method is used to value the price an acquirer may offer a target company, but is generally not used to value an IPO. The other valuation methods may be used to value a company in order to determine its intrinsic value.\
