\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 Valuation using discount cash flow models are based on dividing the present value of the FCF by (1 + WACC). A change in the terminal growth rate will affect the present value of the FCF. A change in valuation will occur if any of the variables affecting either DCF or WACC change. Interest rate changes affect WACC. The repurchase of common stock affects both free cash flow (working capital declines) and WACC (an increase in the debt-to-total capitalization ratio). A change in the market value of common stock affects the enterprise value of a company.\
