\f0\i0 \cf4 \cb6 70\'a0of\'a0110\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb5 The difference between the return on invested capital (ROIC) and the weighted average cost of capital (WACC) is referred to as:\cb1 \
\cb5 QID:\'a02840167\cb1 \
\cb5 Mark For Review\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0\fs60 \cf4 \cb6 A\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf4 \cb6 Accounting profit\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs60 \cf11 \'a0\'a0\'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs34 \cf9 \cb6 Net operating profit after-tax (NOPAT)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0\fs60 \cf4 C\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf4 \cb6 Earnings per share (EPS)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs60 \cf8 \'a0\'a0\'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb6 Economic value added (EVA)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs47\fsmilli23800 \cf12 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl1180\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \cb5 INCORRECT ANSWER CHOSEN\cf12 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 The difference between ROIC and WACC is one way to find the economic value added (EVA). EVA can also be found using this formula: EVA = NOPAT - (WACC x Invested Capital). EVA measures how much value is being created. When ROIC exceeds WACC, economic value is being added because returns exceed the cost of capital.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa272\partightenfactor0

\f8\b \cf4 (18276)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0 \cf4 \cb6 71\'a0of\'a0110\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb5 The S&P 500 has an average P/E of 25. Grind and Muck Industries is trading at 8 times its trailing EPS. Which of the following observations is implied about Grind and Muck?\cb1 \
\cb5 QID:\'a02840192\cb1 \
\cb5 Mark For Review\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0\fs60 \cf4 \cb6 A\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf4 \cb6 The company's earnings are expected to increase\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs60 \cf8 \'a0\'a0\'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs34 \cf9 \cb6 An external influence, such as a major lawsuit, is depressing the price of the company\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0\fs60 \cf4 C\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf4 \cb6 As an industrial company, a low P/E is expected\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\fs60 \cf4 D\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf4 \cb6 The company is highly leveraged\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs47\fsmilli23800 \cf10 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl1180\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \cb5 CORRECT ANSWER CHOSEN\cf10 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 Grind and Muck has a P/E of 8. This is significantly below the S&P 500 average. This would normally indicate a significant influence outside of the normal conditions that affect the stock price. Such external influences include major lawsuits and governmental investigations. Industrial companies generally have a lower P/E than the S&P 500 Index, but not as low as is indicated in the question. If the S&P 500 Index average is 25, an industrial company may be expected to trade at 15 to 18. A low P/E ratio is an indication that the expected growth of earnings is lower than the industry average.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa272\partightenfactor0

