\f0\i0 \cf4 \cb6 73\'a0of\'a0110\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb5 MSD Pharmaceuticals has retained earnings at the end of 2017 of $39,095.1 MM and net income in 2017 of $3,325.5 MM. In 2018, the company's net income increased by 8% and at the end of the year it paid a cash dividend of $3,310.7 MM. What is the 2018 ending balance of the company's retained earnings if it has a 21% tax rate?\cb1 \
\cb5 QID:\'a02840217\cb1 \
\cb5 Mark For Review\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0\fs60 \cf4 \cb6 A\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf4 \cb6 $42,686.6 MM\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\fs60 \cf4 B\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf4 \cb6 $42,405.8 MM\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs60 \cf8 \'a0\'a0\'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs34 \cf9 \cb6 $39,375.9 MM\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0\fs60 \cf4 D\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl600\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf4 \cb6 $39,109.9 MM\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs47\fsmilli23800 \cf10 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl1180\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \cb5 CORRECT ANSWER CHOSEN\cf10 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 The company's tax rate is irrelevant since we are given net income (an after-tax number). The company's net income in 2018 is $3,591.5 MM ($3,325.5 MM x 1.08). The company paid a cash dividend of $3,310.7 MM and, therefore, the difference between the net income and the dividends paid is $280.8 MM ($3,591.5 MM - $3,310.7 MM), which would increase the company's retained earnings. The ending retained earnings balance would be $39,375.9 ($39,095.1 MM + $280.8 MM).\
