\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 Adjusted EBITDA may be used in a potential acquisition. In this example, first multiply EBITDA of 26 by 9, which equals a transactional value of $234 MM. Next, add the $4 MM of synergies to the $26 MM to arrive at adjusted EBITDA of 30. Divide the transactional value by the adjusted EBITDA, which equals 7.8 (234 / 30 = 7.8).\
