\f7\i\b0\fs34 \cf4 \cb5 The formula to calculate enterprise value is Market Capitalization plus Debt (long-term and/or short-term) less Cash and Cash Equivalents. If a company has cash and no debt or less debt than cash, the enterprise value (EV) will be less than the firm's market capitalization. If a company has no cash, the EV would be at least the market value of the stock, plus the value of the debt it had. If the company has less cash than debt, the EV would be greater than the market capitalization.\
